THE RISK:
{
 "id": "per-country-access-stack",
 "title": "The unmodeled per-country access stack — stiftung EAR WEEE numbers, packaging EPR, EORI, Swiss non-EU paperwork — serializes CE entry against a 12-month clock",
 "narrative": "The serviceableFactor derivation admits its cert stack 'justifies <1.0 but doesn't quantify 0.55' and names only three regimes. The corpus itself surfaces a larger stack: WEEE registration (per-country, per-brand — Germany's stiftung EAR alone runs 2–4 months), packaging EPR (VerpackG/LUCID), EORI customs setup, RoHS/REACH documentation — and Switzerland sits outside the EU single market entirely, requiring separate importer and recycling (SENS) arrangements. None of these is individually a 'market risk'; the mechanism is serialization: each country becomes lawfully sellable only after its registrations complete, so within a 12-month window several geographies are unreachable for part or all of the year. That pushes effective Year-1 reach below the band's own low edge, and plausibly removes Switzerland (0.08 of the funnel) from the first-year set altogether.",
 "category": "fact",
 "targetNodes": [
  "serviceableFactor",
  "geo.CH"
 ],
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "First sale in each CE country requires completed country-level registrations: DE WEEE via stiftung EAR (ElektroG), packaging EPR (LUCID), EORI, plus non-EU Switzerland's separate importer/recycling regime — a stack the corpus documents as materially broader than the three regimes the model cites",
   "refs": [
    "digest:serviceable-benchmark#c10",
    "ledger:geo.CH"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "The digest's own tension flags that the fuller stack pushes serviceableFactor toward or below 0.45; but the deeper effect is temporal — registrations serialize country launches, so a pre-launch entrant's lawfully-reachable geography expands stepwise across the very 12 months the YAM measures",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:serviceableFactor",
    "digest:serviceable-benchmark#c12",
    "profile:Stage"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "Year-1 serviceable reach sits below the 0.45 band edge, and the Swiss slice — with its distinct non-EU paperwork and self-operation-heavy buyer base — falls out of the first-year reachable scope entirely",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:serviceableFactor",
    "ledger:geo.CH"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "Each registration is individually trivial — a form and a few thousand euros — so none makes a risk list organized by 'big' instruments. The kill mechanism is their serialization against a fixed 12-month window, which only becomes visible when someone builds the compliance Gantt chart against the sales plan.",
 "expectedObviousness": "medium",
 "falsifier": "A counsel-built compliance timeline showing all CE-7 registrations (EAR, LUCID, national WEEE equivalents, EORI, Swiss importer/SENS setup) are completable in parallel within 90 days pre-launch.",
 "likelihood": {
  "value": 0.55,
  "rationale": "The registrations are legally mandatory and their lead times are documented administrative facts; the base rate of hardware entrants underestimating multi-country EPR/WEEE sequencing is high. Uncertainty is only whether the venture has quietly already started them. [evidence revision: Evidence solidly confirms the mechanism's core factual premises — multi-month WEEE lead times, mandatory pre-sale registration, a broader-than-modeled register stack, foreign authorized-representative requirements, and Switzerland's distinct non-EU regime. This raises confidence in the serialization dynamic slightly above the base-rate prior. The residual uncertainty is unchanged: whether the venture has already started these registrations (unobservable here) and whether use of representatives/agents can compress timelines. EORI being fast is noted but is not the binding constraint. Modest upward revision to 0.55.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.5
 },
 "perturbation": [
  {
   "nodeId": "serviceableFactor",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.42,
   "note": "serialized country access holds Year-1 reach below the band's low edge"
  },
  {
   "nodeId": "geo.CH",
   "op": "exclude",
   "note": "Swiss non-EU compliance setup defers CH to Year 2 — foreclosed from this venture's Year-1 scope, not shrunk"
  }
 ],
 "indicators": [
  {
   "signal": "stiftung EAR registration processing times and backlog",
   "where": "stiftung EAR portal and published registration statistics",
   "threshold": "processing exceeding 3 months for new B2B registrants",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "Whether incumbents maintain distinct Swiss-compliance SKUs and importer structures",
   "where": "Bachmann/Rittal/Vertiv Swiss price lists and Swiss distributor catalogues",
   "threshold": "separate CH SKUs/importer-of-record arrangements visible at ≥2 incumbents",
   "updates": "increases"
  }
 ],
 "mitigations": [
  {
   "action": "Commission a country-by-country market-access memo (registrations, lead times, dependencies) for the CE-7 and convert it into a bottom-up reachable-share model — the node's own promotion path",
   "type": "information",
   "voiNodeId": "serviceableFactor",
   "note": "replaces the unanchored 0.55 with a dated, per-country reach schedule"
  },
  {
   "action": "File DE and NL registrations immediately (covering 0.78 of the funnel) and deliberately sequence CH/PL to Year 2",
   "type": "operational",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": null
  },
  {
   "action": "Contract an EU authorized-representative/importer-of-record service to parallelize the remaining country stacks",
   "type": "contractual",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": null
  }
 ],
 "evidenceStatus": "corroborated",
 "evidence": [
  {
   "title": "Wie lange dauert die Registrierung? (stiftung EAR WEEE)",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Elektrogesetz.de",
   "date": "2019-09-17",
   "excerpt": "Von der Beantragung bis zur Erteilung einer WEEE-Registrierung durch die Stiftung EAR, vergehen weiterhin „mehrere Monate“... etwa 8 bis 10 Wochen... First in, first out; keine beschleunigte Bearbeitung.",
   "url": "https://www.elektrogesetz.de/wie-lange-dauert-die-registrierung/",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "EPR-Nummer in Deutschland beantragen: Schritt fuer Schritt",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Koorvi",
   "date": "2026-06-19",
   "excerpt": "In Deutschland sind es in Wahrheit drei verschiedene Register, drei Nummern und zwei Behoerden... bevor dein erstes Produkt in Deutschland in Verkehr geht.",
   "url": "https://www.koorvi.com/de/blog/epr-nummer-beantragen-deutschland",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "WEEE Schweiz / SENS eRecycling",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "take-e-way / Stiftung SENS",
   "date": "2021-06-29",
   "excerpt": "Die Stiftung SENS organisiert in der Schweiz die Entsorgung von elektronischen Haushaltsgeräten — separate importer/recycling regime for non-EU Switzerland.",
   "url": "https://www.take-e-way.de/news/weee-schweiz-oeffentliche-liste-der-nicht-systemteilnehmer/",
   "attached": true
  }
 ],
 "stances": [
  {
   "url": "https://www.elektrogesetz.de/wie-lange-dauert-die-registrierung/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Von der Beantragung bis zur Erteilung einer WEEE-Registrierung durch die Stiftung EAR, vergehen weiterhin „mehrere Monate“. Aktuell beträgt die effektive Bearbeitungszeit unserer Beobachtung nach etwa 8 bis 10 Wochen"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.stiftung-ear.de/anleitungen/weee-nummer-beantragen-als-auslaendisches-unternehmen/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Möchten Sie als ausländisches Unternehmen Elektro- oder Elektronikgeräte in Deutschland in den Verkehr bringen, können Sie sich nicht selbst registrieren. Sie benötigen dazu einen Bevollmächtigten"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://epr.eldris.ai/de/weee-registrierung-deutschland/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Die Registrierung bei **Stiftung EAR** ist eine zwingende Voraussetzung, bevor elektrische oder elektronische Geräte (EEE) auf dem deutschen Markt angeboten werden können."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.koorvi.com/de/blog/epr-nummer-beantragen-deutschland",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "In Deutschland sind es in Wahrheit drei verschiedene Register, drei Nummern und zwei Behoerden, und wer die falsche vergisst, riskiert bis zu 200.000 Euro Bussgeld und gesperrte Listings."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://for-sure.net/de/pages/epr-importeure",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Werden Waren aus Nicht-EU-Ländern in die EU eingeführt, ist das Unternehmen, das sie in Verkehr bringt, für deren Entsorgung verantwortlich."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.take-e-way.de/news/weee-schweiz-oeffentliche-liste-der-nicht-systemteilnehmer/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Die Stiftung SENS organisiert in der Schweiz die Entsorgung von elektronischen Haushaltsgeräten."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.zoll.de/DE/Fachthemen/Zoelle/EORI-Nummer/Beantragung-einer-EORI-Nummer/beantragung-einer-eori-nummer.html",
   "stance": "silent",
   "quote": "Über das Zoll-Portal können Sie schnell, bequem und medienbruchfrei eine EORI-Nummer beantragen oder selbst ändern."
  }
 ]
}

